This could be useful as well, but I was going for something like:
If Beam Pipeline is: `Read.from(KafkaIO).apply(ParDo.of(new MyDoFn()))....` I'd want a `Visitor` that (instead of executing the pipeline) would simply write the actually applied Spark app as if it was written in Spark (as much as possible), so we get:
`KafkaUtils.createDirectStream(...).mapPartitions(new MyDoFn())...` - in case of other IOs it might be difficult since not all are supportted by Spark, but you could mock something. DoFn implementation details are clearly opaque too.
It's mostly a debug tool.
